aders 1939\u20131945===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name<ref>Sources: 41 Squadron Operations Record Book (TNA AIR 27/425-426) and 'Escape/Evasion Reports: Code MI9/SPG' (TNA WO 208)</ref> !! Period !! Details\n|-\n| WINSKILL, Archie L. || Aug\u2013Nov 1941 ||  Evaded and returned to UK\n|-\n| SLACK, Thomas A. H.  || Jul\u2013Aug 1943 ||  Evaded and returned to UK\n|-\n| Prickett, Leslie A.  || Aug\u2013Dec 1943 ||  Evaded for four months, but captured\n|-\n| MAY, Stanley H. || Sep\u2013Oct 1943 ||  Evaded and returned to UK\n|-\n| PARRY, Hugh L.  || Sep 1943 \u2013 Mar 1944 ||  Evaded for six months, but captured\n|-\n| STOK, Bram van der  || March 1944 ||  Escaped in \u2018Great Escape\u2019 & returned to UK\n|}\n\n===Guinea Pig Club members===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name<ref>Sources: 41 Squadron Operations Record Book (TNA AIR 27/424-426) and 'McIndoe's Army; The injured airmen who faced the world', Peter Williams & Ted Harison, Pelham Books, 1979, {{ISBN|0 7207 1191 6}}.</ref> !! Date of Injury !! Service on 41 Sqn\n|-\n| [[George Bennions|BENNIONS, George H.]] || 1 October 1940 ||  16 February 1936 \u2013 1 October 1940\n|-\n| LANE, Roy  || 26 August 1940 ||  6 April-ca 27 September 1943\n|-\n| [[Eric Lock|LOCK, Eric S.]]  || 17 November 1940 ||  18 June-17 November 1940\n|-\n| WHALE, F. Victor || 11 December 1944 ||  7 March 1945 \u2013 12 February 1946\n|-\n| WOOLLARD, Frederick G.  || 18 July 1944 ||  18 December 1943 \u2013 18 July 1944\n|}\n\n===Roll of Honour 1916\u20132016===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name<ref>Sources: Commonwealth War Graves Commission, 41 Squadron Operations Records Books 1916\u20131946 (TNA AIR 1/1791/204/153/1-4, TNA AIR 1/1792/204/153/5-6, 8 & 10, & TNA AIR 27/424-426), 'Air Ministry and Successors: Civil Aviation Accident Reports (C, W, and S Reports) and Technical Memoranda' (TNA AVIA 5), and Air Accident Report Cards, Air Ministry Form 1180 (RAF Museum).</ref> !! Nationality !! Date !!  !! Name !! Nationality