ick Huskinson]], CBE, MC & Bar<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rafweb.org/Biographies/Huskinson.htm |title=Air Commodore Patrick Huskinson | first=M. B. |last=Barrass |work=Air of Authority \u2013 A History of RAF Organisation |accessdate=11 February 2016}}</ref> || 6 February 1930 ||  || William Kent AFC || 1 September 1965\n|-\n| [[Stanley Vincent|Stanley Flamank Vincent]], CB, DFC, AFC<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rafweb.org/Biographies/VincentS.htm |title=Air Vice Marshal Stanley Flamank Vincent| first=M. B. |last=Barrass |work=Air of Authority \u2013 A History of RAF Organisation |accessdate=11 February 2016}}</ref> || 24 October 1931 ||  || Henry Ellis Angell DFC <ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.207squadron.rafinfo.org.uk/angell/angell-celebrate.htm |title=A Celebration of the Life of Wg Cdr HE 'Bill' Angell DFC RAF (Retd) |first=Frank |last=Haslam |work=207 Squadron RAF History |year=2013 |accessdate=11 February 2016}}</ref> || January 1966\n|-\n| John Auguste Boret, CBE, MC, AFC<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rafweb.org/Biographies/Boret.htm |title=Air Vice Marshal John Auguste Boret | first=M. B. |last=Barrass |work=Air of Authority \u2013 A History of RAF Organisation |accessdate=11 February 2016}}</ref> || 1 May 1933 ||  || George Henry Dodd || August 1968\n|-\n| John Simon Leslie Adams || 4 March 1937 ||  || Brian James Lemon MBE, AFC<ref>{{cite web |url=http://announcements.telegraph.co.uk/deaths/170597/lemon |title=Deaths Announcements: Lemon |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=2 November 2013 |accessdate=11 February 2016}}</ref> || 1 April 1972\n|-\n| Geoffrey Augustus Graydon Johnston, CBE || 28 August 1939 ||  || Peter David Leonard Gover MBE, AFC, BSc || March 1974\n|-\n| [[Hilary Hood|Hilary Richard Lionel Hood]], DFC<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/history/ww2peopleswar/stories/17/a2045017.shtml |title=What Happened to Squadron Leader Robin Hood? |work=BBC \u2013 WW2 People's War |date=15 November 2003 |accessdate=11 February 2016}}</ref> 